# Homepage Redesign: Vercel Aesthetic

Redesign the homepage to capture the sleek, high-performance aesthetic of Vercel.com while maintaining all existing content and translations.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Global Styles
#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/app/globals.css)
- Refine the color palette for deeper blacks and cleaner grays in dark mode.
- Add custom utilities for:
    - **Radiant Borders**: Subtle glowing borders on hover.
    - **Spotlight Backgrounds**: Smooth radial gradients.
    - **Text Gradients**: High-contrast heading styles.

### [Component] Navigation
#### [MODIFY] [LandingHeader.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/containers/landing/LandingHeader.tsx)
- Enhance the transparency and backdrop-blur effects.
- Simplify vertical padding and border weight.
- Add a subtle "active" state or hover glow to nav items.

### [Component] Hero Section
#### [MODIFY] [Hero.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/containers/landing/Hero.tsx)
- Implement a bolder, more dramatic layout.
- Use larger typography with tighter tracking.
- Add a "Spotlight" effect that follows the mouse or pulses subtly.
- Improve the secondary button (outline) to feel more premium.

### [Component] Features Section (Bento Grid)
#### [NEW] [BentoGrid.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/BentoGrid.tsx)
- Create a reusable Bento Grid component.
#### [MODIFY] [LandingFeatures.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/containers/landing/LandingFeatures.tsx)
- Transition from a single image to a rich Bento Grid showcasing the four main features:
    - AI Agent
    - Deep Research
    - Analytics
    - Project Management

### [Component] Performance & Animations
- Optimize `framer-motion` transitions to be smoother and more "viscous" (Vercel style).
- Use `Inter` font with corrected weights or integrate `Geist` if approved.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Font Selection**: The project currently uses `Inter`. Vercel uses `Geist`. Should I attempt to integrate `Geist` or just optimize the current `Inter` typography?

> [!NOTE]
> **Layout Logic**: I will be converting the "What We Do" and "Features" sections into more of a unified "Showcase" using a Bento Grid layout. This will keep the content but present it more dynamically.

## Open Questions
1. Do you have a preference for the dark mode background? (e.g., Pure Black #000 vs. Very Dark Gray #0a0a0a).
2. Should I maintain the "Orb Gradient" or move towards more subtle "Linear Gradients"?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Build check: `npm run build`
- Lint check: `npm run lint`

### Manual Verification
- Visual inspection on desktop and mobile viewports.
- Interact with all hover states and transitions to ensure they feel premium.
- Verify that light mode still looks great (though Vercel aesthetic prioritizes dark mode).
